Measure v1.0

Copyright (c) 2011 Martijn W. van der Lee
Licensed under the MIT.

Measure an amount of CSS3 units in pixels, relative to a specified context if available.
Based on http://www.filamentgroup.com/lab/update_jquery_plugin_for_retaining_scalable_interfaces_with_pixel_to_em_con/

Syntax:
	$(<context>).measure(<size>);
	$.measure(<size>);
	
Arguments:
	context	(optional)	The DOM tree node in which to measure. Some units like 'em' and '%' are relative to the current font size.
						If not specified, 'body' will be used for units that require a context.
	size	(optional)	A number and CSS3 unit or constant that should be measured.
						The number can be integer or floating point and may be preceded by a sign (-/+). It acts as a multiplier for a single unit.
						The unit can be any of the following:
							px, in, cm, mm, pt, pc						(no context)
							em, ex, rem									(uses context)
							vw, vh, vm									(no context)
							thin, thick									(border widths)
							border-thin, border-medium, border-thick	(alternative names for border widths)
							%											(relative to current font-size, uses context)
							xx-small, x-small, small, medium,
								large, x-large, xx-large				(font-size names, no context)
							smaller, larger								(relative font-size names, uses context)							
						Both the number and unit/constant are optional; number will default to '1', unit will default to 'em'.
	
Return:
	pixels	The measured size in pixel units.
			If the unit is specified but not recognized, an error will be thrown.

Examples:
	$.measure();				// returns the current font-size (1em) set in <body>, measured in pixels.
	$.measure('thin');			// returns the "thin" border-width, measured in pixels.
	$.measure('small');			// returns the "small" font-size. measured in pixels.
	$.measure('2in');			// returns the number of pixels in 2 inches.
	$.measure('200%');			// returns the number of pixels in a font-size 200% the size of the font in <body>.
	$('#here').measure('200%');	// returns the number of pixels in a font-size 200% the size of the font in the tag with id "here".
	$('#here').measure('in');	// returns the number of pixels in an inch. The context is ignored.